<!-- Panel -->
<section class="panel color2-alt">
	<div class="intro color2">
		<h2 class="major">Ruby</h2>
		<p>We're going to start with some of the exercises from the Ruby track. Look for each individual exercise on the Exercism website.</p>
	</div>
	<div class="inner columns divided">
		<div class="span-2">
			<h3 class="major">Exercise #1: Hello World</h3>
			<p>This exercise is just to help you get used to Exercism. You'll learn how to write code to get the automated tests to pass and how to submit your solution.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="span-2">
			<h3 class="major">Exercise #2: Raindrops</h3>
			<p>This exercise may seem like another you may have seen before...</p>
		</div>
		<div class="span-2">
			<h3 class="major">Exercise #3: Beer Song</h3>
			<p>This exercise involves some logic, but the trickiest part is actually the text wrangling.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="span-2">
			<h3 class="major">Exercise #4: Leap</h3>
			<p>The good ol' leap year calculator!</p>
		</div>
		<div class="span-2">
			<h3 class="major">Exercise #5: Hamming</h3>
			<p>You'll have to develop a fun little algorithm for this one.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="span-2">
			<h3 class="major">Exercise #6: Etl</h3>
			<p>This exercise is a great refresher on maniuplating data structures like arrays and hashes.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="span-2">
			<h3 class="major">Exercise #7: Grade School</h3>
			<p>This exercise is heavy on OOP, so is a perfect refresher if you want to brush up on that area.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<!-- Panel -->
<section class="panel color4-alt">
	<div class="intro color4">
		<h2 class="major">JavaScript</h2>
		<p>Now that you have the hang of Exercism, it's good to try it out on a second programming language as well. Join the JavaScript track to access these exercises. There's plenty of repeats from the Ruby track, but there are some exercises unique to the JavaScript track as well.</p>
	</div>
	<div class="inner columns divided">
		<div class="span-2">
			<h3 class="major">Exercise #1: Hello World</h3>
			<p>This will get you used to working with the JavaScript track.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="span-2">
			<h3 class="major">Exercise #2: Two Fer</h3>
			<p>This one is easy, and helps ease you more into working with the JavaScript exercises.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="span-2">
			<h3 class="major">Exercise #3: Darts</h3>
			<p>If you love darts, you'll love this exercise. If you love circles, you'll love this exercise. If you love programming, you'll love this exercise. If you love all three, then you should marry this exercise.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="span-2">
			<h3 class="major">Exercise #4: Grade School</h3>
			<p>You may have already done this exercise in the Ruby track, but it's great for your JavaScript chops to convert your existing solution to JavaScript code.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

